  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Last year my score for CAT was around 40 percentile. What should I do to score > 90  percentile this year?",
  "response": "Improving your CAT score from 40 percentile to over 90 percentile requires a strategic and focused approach. Here are some steps you can follow to achieve this goal:\n\n1. **Understand the Exam Pattern and Syllabus:**\n   - Familiarize yourself with the CAT exam structure, which includes three sections: Verbal Ability and Reading Comprehension (VARC), Data Interpretation and Logical Reasoning (DILR), and Quantitative Ability (QA).\n   - Thoroughly review the syllabus and identify the key topics in each section.\n\n2. **Assessment of Current Level:**\n   - Take a diagnostic test to identify your strengths and weaknesses. This will help you create a personalized study plan.\n\n3. **Create a Study Plan:**\n   - Allocate time wisely to each section based on your strengths and weaknesses.\n   - Set aside regular study hours each day and adhere to a consistent schedule.\n   - Break down your preparation into phases, such as concept building, practice, testing, and revision.\n\n4. **Build Strong Concepts:**\n   - Focus on understanding the fundamental concepts, especially in Quantitative Ability and Logical Reasoning.\n   - For VARC, improve vocabulary, grammar, and reading comprehension skills.\n\n5. **Practice Regularly:**\n   - Solve a variety of problems in each section to build expertise.\n   - Attempt previous year CAT papers and sample questions to become familiar with the question patterns.\n\n6. **Take Mock Tests:**\n   - Regularly take full-length mock tests to simulate exam conditions.\n   - Analyze your performance after each mock test to identify areas for improvement.\n   - Aim to gradually decrease the time taken and increase accuracy.\n\n7. **Improve Time Management:**\n   - Practice time management skills to ensure you can complete all questions within the time limits during the actual exam.\n   - Focus on developing quick calculation skills for the QA section and efficient reading strategies for VARC.\n\n8. **Focus on Accuracy and Strategy:**\n   - Work towards improving accuracy to minimize negative marking.\n   - Develop a strategy on how to attempt questions, including which questions to attempt first and which to skip.\n\n9. **Revise Regularly:**\n   - Set aside time for regular revision to consolidate concepts and formulas.\n   - Maintain notes for important formulas, tricks, and shortcuts.\n\n10. **Stay Updated and Motivated:**\n    - Engage with CAT preparation forums and groups to stay updated and motivated.\n    - Seek guidance from mentors or join coaching if necessary.\n\n11. **Take Care of Yourself:**\n    - Ensure you are eating well, sleeping adequately, and taking breaks to maintain physical and mental health.\n\nBy diligently following these steps and staying committed to your preparation, you can significantly improve your CAT percentile. Remember, consistent effort and the right strategy are key to success.",
